tabularise v0.3.0

Tabularise an object (arrange or enter in tabular form)

Source: R/tabularise.R
tabularise.Rd

Tabularise an object (arrange or enter in tabular form)

Usage

tabularise(data, ..., type = "default", env = parent.frame())

tabularize(data, ..., type = "default", env = parent.frame())

Arguments

data

An object

...

Further arguments (depending on the object class and on type=).

type

The type of table to produce.

env

The environment where to evaluate formulas (you probably do not need to change the default).

Value

A flextable object you can print in different form or rearrange with the flextable functions from set Stb$verb().

See also

tabularise_default(), tabularise_headtail(), tabularise_coef(), tabularise_tidy(), tabularise_glance()

Examples

tabularise(iris)
